&lt;html&gt;&lt;div style=&#39;background-color:&#39;&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;(OOC: I wanted to do a big giant, spec-fackin&#39;-tacular post for my return, but then Rauq told me I had to come in with a stasis pod.&nbsp; Since I&#39;ve done that so many times I&#39;d rather die than write a lot about a stasis pod.&nbsp; Plus Rauq&#39;s a lazy bitch and didn&#39;t give me a whole lot of info on the pods :) )&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;With the battle raging on the surface of the planet Earth between the Predacons and the Tripredacus, right on the very doorstep of the place the Tripreds call home, another event takes place a long distance away.&nbsp; Not as important as Megatron&#39;s attempts to obliterate the nuisance of the Tripredacus, but an event nonetheless.&nbsp; But it is not on another continent nor in the depths of a salt-filled ocean.&nbsp; No, this great distance is upwards.&nbsp; Higher than where eagles dare and higher than the heavens, out in the dark vastness of space where the Maximal stasis pods circle the Earth in their almost never ending dance with its gravity.&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Almost &lt;/EM&gt;neverending.&nbsp; For one of these few dark pods, the little dance is coming to an end as Earth&#39;s gravity gains a stronger grasp on it and pulls it closer and closer towards its atmosphere.&nbsp; It&#39;s only a few minutes before the darkness of the stasis pod is clashing with the blue, cloudless skies of Earth as it&nbsp;continues falling.&nbsp;&nbsp;It descends at a rapid pace which only increases as the seconds tick by and the pod comes closer to impacting with the solid surface of Tripredacus territory.&nbsp; Of course, by the&nbsp;day&#39;s end, it may become Predacon territory.&nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;Falling faster than a diving bird,&nbsp;much of the dark pod begins to glow with a redness from the increasing heat.&nbsp; If&nbsp;scans did not reveal the pod to any base when it first began to descent,&nbsp;they certainly have by now.&nbsp; But you do not need&nbsp;the sensors of a powerful base to see the dark object hurtling towards the ground or to hear its whistling.&nbsp; The pod hits the ground, still not coming to a halt as it digs into the ground, burying itself halfway in its very own crater.&nbsp; Only a&nbsp;few hundred yards away are the members of the Predacon faction, the&nbsp;Maximal pod screaming to be reprogrammed and used for their dastardly devices.&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
